    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="744"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d744">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11776a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to certain
                            <gloss type="to">American diplomatic missions</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="22" xml:id="d744fn22">Sent to the missions in Argentina,
                        Austria-Hungary, Belgium, Brazil, Chile, Costa Rica, Cuba, Denmark, France,
                        Germany, Great Britain, Guatemala, Honduras, Italy, Japan, Netherlands,
                        Nicaragua, Norway, Paraguay, Peru, Portugal, Russia, Salvador, Spain, Sweden
                        and Uruguay.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Mediators have notified the State Department that both Huerta and Carranza
                    have accepted the principle of mediation.<note n="23" xml:id="d744fn23">As to
                        Carranza’s attitude, see post, the inclosures with the Special
                        Commissioners’ despatch No. 8, May 31.</note> This enables the Mediators to
                    deal with the entire Mexican situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
